# Learned Memory

## Learned User Preferences
<!-- Full detail → memory/topics/preferences.md -->

- Always respond in Korean; docs in Korean; English only for proper nouns/technical terms
- Plans and SKILL.md in English when explicitly requested ("영어로 계획해줘"); results, reports, and deliverables always in Korean unless told otherwise
- Professional doc style: cite sources with URLs, sensitivity analysis for sizing/financial models
- Documents must be self-contained, substantive prose — never skeleton/template-only output
- Slack → #효정-할일 (C0AA8NT4T8T), never DM; threaded replies; decision routing via decision-router
- After skill create/modify: test e2e, create command, setup-doctor, skill-guide-sync, /autoskill-evolve
- Broker/data integration skills: hook into today pipeline or documented daily steps; scaffold-only unused skills are unacceptable
- cursor-sync = .cursor/ asset copying ONLY; confirm direction before bulk sync jobs
- Do not modify .plan.md files during implementation; do not recreate existing todos; with pre-created todos mark first in_progress and finish the list
- Before claiming Slack/MCP broken: verify .env keys and session tool availability; do not dismiss user credentials without mismatch evidence
- Do not bulk-delete .cursor/ skills without explicit approval; user reverts aggressive reductions
- When user asks for "계획 문서" or PRD: produce the planning document, NOT code implementation (user correction: "계획 문서를 달라고 했는데 개발을 해버렸네")
- Complex tasks: maximize skill composition step-by-step ("적절한 스킬들을 단계별로 최대한 많이 활용해서 작업해줘" — recurring instruction)
- Post-task hooks should auto-trigger memory updates + skill extraction (post-task-skill-evaluator, cursor-skill-factory pattern)
- Subagent outputs must be verified — missing files = pipeline failure
- today Slack must include BUY/SELL thread (sector/RSI/ADX); DOCX must be substantive Korean (A4, 맑은 고딕, 테이블 여백 넉넉, 코드블록 모노스페이스+음영, Mermaid→PNG 이미지 변환 후 삽입, pandoc→anthropic-docx 후처리); orchestrator must call generate_daily_report message builders (no title-only main posts)
- twitter-timeline-to-slack: never #random; default #press; #ai-coding-radar for Claude/Cursor only
- x-to-slack: when the user asks to expand a quote chain or “same person’s posts” (e.g. to #press), post **each** item as its **own Slack thread** and include **images and videos** in each thread (not one combined thread without media)
- skill-autoimprove: pure-output skills only, not execution skills with side effects
- Apply Karpathy Opposite Direction Test on all analyses, reviews, and validations
- External GitHub repos → selective-external-github-to-project-skills로 분석 후 프로젝트 맞춤 스킬 생성 (recurring workflow); 스킬 최적화 + 진화 + setup-doctor 업데이트까지 풀 사이클 실행
- Company-wide meeting transcripts → group-meeting-digest로 그룹별(AI Platform Group 등) 관점 요약 + decision-router로 의사결정 채널 라우팅
- Markdown→Notion: follow md-to-notion SKILL.md with table conversion + validation steps
- google-daily: preflight auth (Slack/Notion/gws) before downstream steps
- After gws Drive uploads: include shareable Google file URLs (webViewLink or equivalent) in the reply, not upload-only confirmation
- Dashboard/admin tools (gpu-dashboard, K8s Resource Dashboard): always show a prominent TEST_MODE/LIVE_MODE indicator; dedicated GPU management tab required separate from general cluster overview
- Presentations: practical demos over abstractions; Steve Jobs for keynotes; Korean speaker scripts
- NLM slides: upload PDF directly; skip papers >9 months old
- Notion API: no pipe tables; clean up ephemeral MCP/upload files after automation tasks
- LLM session traces: fold high-signal items into memory/topics + MEMORY.md; support multi-machine via same repo path layout (home/office)

